text: September unemployment rates ranged from 2.0% in NE to 7.5% in CA and NV.
GDP growth between Q2 2020 and Q2 2021 ranged from 6.6% in Alaska to 18.1% in Tennessee.
In Q2 2021, 35 states saw their greatest annual house price growth in three decades.
Leisure and hospitality jobs in September 2021 were above prepandemic levels in only Idaho.
Among states, average private weekly earnings in September ranged from $807 in MS to $1,260 in MA.
Michigan and 35 other states saw manufacturing GDP exceed prepandemic levels in Q2 2021.
In September 2021, GA and NE saw their lowest unemployment rates in over 45 years.
From Q2 2020 to Q2 2021, house price increases ranged from 8.2% in AK to 37.1% in ID.
RI’s public education jobs were 10% above September 2020 but 5% below September 2019.
In Q2 2021, Washington State saw the highest growth in total GDP from prepandemic levels.
